  animalID: Ndugu
  animalName: Ndugu
  species: African Bush Elephant
  scientificName: 'Loxodonta africana '
  status: 0
  biome: 0
  portrait: {fileID: 0}
  journalArt: {fileID: 0}
  introDialogue: "YOU ARE ONE OF THEM. Wait, no. You smell... different. My name
    is Ndugu. I've walked this land for 47 years. When I was young,\nthis river ran
    year-round. My herd's watering hole\nthe one my grandmother taught me  has a
    poaching camp on it now. My calves cannot drink safely.\n\nI cannot fight them
    myself. But you look like you can.\t"
  questDialogue: 'The camp is just ahead. Drive them out and the water is safe again.
    That is all I ask. I just want for these lands to be safer for my calves before
    I die

'
  completionDialogue: The water is clean again. I will not forget this. Neither will
    my herd. Elephants remember everything  the good and the bad. You have done something
    real today.
  journalEntry: 'African Bush Elephant | Loxodonta africana

    Status: Vulnerable
    - 415,000 remain in the wild


    Elephants are the architects of their ecosystems.
    They dig waterholes used by dozens of other species, disperse seeds across hundreds
    of kilometres, and knock down trees that create clearings for smaller animals.


    When
    elephants disappear, the entire landscape changes.


    The main threats are
    habitat loss, human-wildlife

    conflict, and ivory poaching. Despite a 1989
    international ivory ban, illegal trade continues, driven by demand in Asia and
    enabled by corruption at borders.


    What you can do: Never buy ivory. Support
    the African

    Wildlife Foundation at awf.org'
  conservationFact: An elephant can recognize its own reflection, something only
    a handful of species can do.
  doofNote: 'Elephants have been observed mourning their dead for days, touching
    the bones of deceased family members. Science has no better word for this than
    grief. Also fun fact: Ndugu means friend or relative in Swahili!'
  questType: 0
  linkedQuiz: {fileID: 0}
  rewardItemID: ReforestationSeed
